<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Chinese_language&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1" title="Edit section: Varieties of Chinese">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline" id="Varieties_of_Chinese">Varieties of Chinese</span></h2>
<div class="rellink relarticle mainarticle">Main article: <a href="/wiki/Varieties_of_Chinese" title="Varieties of Chinese">Varieties of Chinese</a></div>
<div class="rellink boilerplate seealso">See also: <a href="/wiki/List_of_Chinese_dialects" title="List of Chinese dialects" class="mw-redirect">List of Chinese dialects</a></div>
<p>A map below depicts the linguistic subdivisions ("languages" or "dialect groups") within China itself. The traditionally recognized seven main groups, in order of population size are<sup class="Template-Fact" title="This claim needs references to reliable sources from April 2011" style="white-space:nowrap;">[<i><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Citation_needed" title="Wikipedia:Citation needed">citation needed</a></i>]</sup>:</p>
